article.headline: Texas State 85, Northwestern St. 81
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas (AP) -- Brandon Bush scored 21 points and Brandon Thomas had 15 to help Texas State beat Northwestern State 85-81 on Thursday night. Antwoine Blanchard added 14 points and Matt Fullenwider had 11 for Texas State (6-8, 1-0 Southland Conference), which led by as many as 15. Keithan Hancock led Northwestern State (5-8, 0-1) with 19 points in just 17 minutes. Kennan Jones scored 14 points and Luke Rogers had 10. The win was Texas State's first in a conference opener in three years and snapped a three-game losing streak to Northwestern State, last season's Southland Conference champion.
